Q: Set Data Twice in react-signature-canvas A: <p>The library's <code>fromData</code> doesn't handle being called twice in quick succession, and the second call wipes everything before it finishes drawing.</p>
<p>Just guard against the double-call:</p>
<pre><code>const dataLoaded = useRef(false);

useEffect(() =&gt; {
  if (!sigCanvas.current || dataLoaded.current) return;

  sigCanvas.current.fromData(data);
  dataLoaded.current = true;

  return () =&gt; {
    dataLoaded.current = false;
  };
}, [data]);
</code></pre>
<p>The ref blocks the second Strict Mode call. The cleanup resets it so real remounts still work.</p>

Q: How to draw proper logic gate curves (OR/NOR shapes) using quadratic Bezier curves in wxWidgets? A: <p>In short, there are many reasons to choose SVG as the basis (or inspiration) for your data structure such as easy visualization or editing in graphic applications.</p>
<p>Fortunately, the &quot;core-concepts&quot; of Bézier (quadratic or cubic) descriptions are quite universal – regardless of the description language or object model.</p>
<p>While the notation structure can vary significantly we can usually translate graphics quite easily.</p>
<h3>Visual debugging via SVG</h3>
<p>Based on you JSON example you could create a rendered output in SVG based on the exact same x/y coordinates:</p>
<ul>
<li>p0 =&gt; SVG <code>M</code> (Moveto – where to start drawing – introducing a new sub-shape)</li>
<li>p1 =&gt; SVG <code>Q</code> 1. quadratic Bézier control point</li>
<li>p2 =&gt; SVG <code>Q</code> 2. quadratic Bézier control point</li>
</ul>
<h3>Segment continuity</h3>
<p>In your example we can easily connect all segments to get a continuous closed shape by omitting new start points:</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
